CAPITAL CITIES/ABC Inc. disputes an analyst's suggestion that the network might find it easier to boost advertising rates because of an increase in the number of anti-drug public service announcements.
The company explains that the public service broadcasts don't displace commercials. 

(See: "Heard on the Street: Thermedics, Like Issues May Gain From War on Drugs, Wall Street Sharpshooters Contend" -- WSJ Sept. 29, 1989) 

